verbose_text: The BPQD-LSD1 siRNA complex exhibited superior transfection efficiency compared to commercial delivery reagents (e.g., Lipofectamine 2000 and Oligofectamine) and was able to inhibit the cell growth rate by> 80% in combination with NIR light with negligible cytotoxicity, indicating the potential of applying BPQD for siRNA delivery and cancer therapy.
